  "description": "Atlas supports secretless authentication for using Azure (Microsoft Azure) Key\nVault (AKV (Azure Key Vault)) with Encryption at Rest (EAR). With this model, you don't\nneed to provide Atlas with long-lived static credentials (Tenant\nID, Client ID, and Client Secret). Instead, you authorize an\nAtlas-managed Azure (Microsoft Azure) Service Principal in your Azure (Microsoft Azure) tenant,\nand Atlas authenticates to AKV (Azure Key Vault) using short-lived OAuth 2.0 access\ntokens that Azure (Microsoft Azure) Active Directory (Azure (Microsoft Azure) AD) issues.",
